between the molecules to get in there.

1563
01:39:38,650 --> 01:39:40,698
Get away from us!

1564
01:39:42,570 --> 01:39:43,571
Daddy, help!

1565
01:39:43,650 --> 01:39:45,254
I love you, Cassie.

1566
01:39:49,050 --> 01:39:50,051
(GRUNTS)

1567
01:40:01,330 --> 01:40:02,855
(SCREAMING)

1568
01:40:15,010 --> 01:40:16,455
Daddy, where are you?

1569
01:40:16,530 --> 01:40:18,020
(VOICE ECHOING)

1570
01:40:18,090 --> 01:40:20,013
HANK: <i>You could go subatomic.</i>

1571
01:40:20,090 --> 01:40:21,330
<i>You could go subatomic.</i>

1572
01:40:22,370 --> 01:40:23,610
Oh, no.

1573
01:40:35,530 --> 01:40:38,136
HANK: <i>You would enter a reality</i>

1574
01:40:38,210 --> 01:40:41,976
<i>where all concepts of time and space...</i>

1575
01:40:42,450 --> 01:40:46,739
<i>All concepts of time and space
become irrelevant.</i>

1576
01:40:48,730 --> 01:40:52,655
<i>...all concepts of time and space
become irrelevant.</i>

1577
01:40:56,730 --> 01:40:58,812
CASSIE: (VOICE DISTORTED)
<i>Come back, Daddy!</i>

1578
01:40:59,610 --> 01:41:06,175
HANK: (VOICE ECHOING)
<i>...as you shrink for all eternity.</i>

1579
01:41:07,730 --> 01:41:10,415
<i>Everything that you know</i>

1580
01:41:12,370 --> 01:41:14,099
<i>and love,</i>

1581
01:41:15,130 --> 01:41:17,053
<i>gone forever.</i>

1582
01:41:17,490 --> 01:41:19,060
CASSIE: <i>Daddy, where are you?</i>

1583
01:41:33,929 --> 01:41:35,977
(CASSIE SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)

1584
01:41:37,249 --> 01:41:38,330
<i>Where are you?</i>

1585
01:41:41,169 --> 01:41:42,614
<i>Where are you?</i>

1586
01:41:43,809 --> 01:41:45,618
<i>- Daddy!</i>
- Cassie.

1587
01:41:53,289 --> 01:41:54,859
<i>Come back, Daddy!</i>

1588
01:41:58,969 --> 01:42:01,620
HANK: <i>Do not screw with the regulator!</i>

1589
01:42:19,569 --> 01:42:20,934
(WIND HOWLING)

1590
01:42:32,169 --> 01:42:34,058
Daddy!

1591
01:42:37,249 --> 01:42:38,819
I love you so much.

1592
01:42:39,529 --> 01:42:40,690
I love you, too.

1593
01:42:41,369 --> 01:42:42,450
So much.

1594
01:42:42,529 --> 01:42:43,974
(PAXTON CLEARS THROAT)

1595
01:42:46,849 --> 01:42:48,489
You know, there's a big hole in the roof.

1596
01:42:51,689 --> 01:42:52,850
Sorry.

1597
01:42:55,649 --> 01:42:57,617
- GALE: Is she all right?
- Yeah, she's fine.

1598
01:42:59,689 --> 01:43:00,690
Mommy!

1599
01:43:03,569 --> 01:43:05,173
PAXTON: She's fine, she's fine.

1600
01:43:14,529 --> 01:43:16,099
HANK: <i>Scott, please.</i>

1601
01:43:16,769 --> 01:43:18,658
You don't remember anything?

1602
01:43:18,729 --> 01:43:19,890
Hank. I don't.

1603
01:43:20,009 --> 01:43:22,376
There must be something else.

1604
01:43:24,089 --> 01:43:27,218
Well, I suppose the human mind

1605
01:43:27,289 --> 01:43:29,974
just can't comprehend the experience,

1606
01:43:32,049 --> 01:43:33,380
but you made it.

1607
01:43:34,049 --> 01:43:35,699
You went in,

1608
01:43:37,049 --> 01:43:38,778
and you got out.

1609
01:43:40,969 --> 01:43:42,573
It's amazing.

1610
01:43:43,249 --> 01:43:45,013
Scott,

1611
01:43:45,089 --> 01:43:47,012
I'll walk you out.

1612
01:43:50,969 --> 01:43:52,494
Get some rest.

1613
01:43:59,369 --> 01:44:00,655
(DOOR CLOSES)

1614
01:44:00,729 --> 01:44:03,130
Is it possible?

1615
01:44:11,809 --> 01:44:13,049
(GROANS)

1616
01:44:21,009 --> 01:44:22,056
When did this happen?

1617
01:44:22,129 --> 01:44:23,255
Nothing's happening.

1618
01:44:23,329 --> 01:44:25,570
Whoa. Hold on.
Something's kind of happening.

1619
01:44:25,649 --> 01:44:27,697
Well, if that's the case,

1620
01:44:27,769 --> 01:44:29,294
shoot me again.

1621
01:44:29,649 --> 01:44:32,255
Yeah. I don't know what you were doing,
grabbing and kissing me like that.

1622
01:44:32,329 --> 01:44:34,252
I'm a little surprised myself.

1623
01:44:34,329 --> 01:44:36,696
I have to get somewhere.
I'll see you later, Hank.

1624
01:44:36,769 --> 01:44:38,259
Really, Hope.

1625
01:44:39,089 --> 01:44:40,454
- Scott.
- Yeah?

1626
01:44:41,049 --> 01:44:42,778
- You're full of shit.
- Oh, yeah.

1627
01:44:44,209 --> 01:44:46,132
PAXTON: Scott,
I met with my captain today.

1628
01:44:46,209 --> 01:44:48,894
He wanted a report on the night
that you got out of jail.

1629
01:44:49,529 --> 01:44:50,969
Something happened with the cameras.

1630
01:44:51,689 --> 01:44:53,896
Some circuits got fried.

1631
01:44:55,009 --> 01:44:57,250
But I told him that
you were processed correctly.

1632
01:44:57,329 --> 01:44:58,455
Really?

1633
01:44:58,529 --> 01:44:59,974
PAXTON: Well, yeah.

1634
01:45:01,769 --> 01:45:04,693
Can't be sending Cassie's dad
back to jail on a technical glitch, right?

1635
01:45:04,769 --> 01:45:06,737
Thank you, Paxton.

1636
01:45:06,809 --> 01:45:08,254
I'm blown away.

1637
01:45:09,049 --> 01:45:10,858
Thank you for everything
you do for Cassie.

1638
01:45:10,929 --> 01:45:12,977
Well, that's my pleasure.

1639
01:45:14,209 --> 01:45:17,338
But, no. This one, I did for you.

1640
01:45:19,369 --> 01:45:20,780
- This is awkward.
- Yeah.

1641
01:45:20,849 --> 01:45:22,658
- Yeah.
- (LAUGHING)

1642
01:45:22,729 --> 01:45:24,219
I mean, what do we even talk about
after all of that?

1643
01:45:24,289 --> 01:45:25,654
- Oh, I know.
- What?

1644
01:45:25,729 --> 01:45:28,300
- I did my first cartwheel today.
- What?

1645
01:45:28,369 --> 01:45:30,975
Yeah. She has been practicing all week.

1646
01:45:31,049 --> 01:45:32,460
But today was the magic day.

1647
01:45:32,529 --> 01:45:33,809
I recorded it on my phone. Here.

1648
01:45:35,249 --> 01:45:37,570
SCOTT: No, that can't be Cassie.
That's not you.

1649
01:45:37,689 --> 01:45:39,289
MAGGIE: Yeah, it is.
CASSIE: Yeah, it is.

1650
01:45:39,329 --> 01:45:41,457
SCOTT: This is a professional gymnast.
There is no way that's you.

1651
01:45:41,569 --> 01:45:42,695
PAXTON: Yeah, that's her.

1652
01:45:43,649 --> 01:45:45,219
Good boy.

1653
01:45:47,129 --> 01:45:49,860
Sweetie, that's pretty amazing, peanut.

1654
01:45:49,929 --> 01:45:51,533
(CELL PHONE VIBRATING)

1655
01:45:52,809 --> 01:45:53,810
Sorry.

1656
01:45:55,489 --> 01:45:57,218
It's work.

1657
01:45:57,849 --> 01:45:59,135
Yeah.

1658
01:46:00,849 --> 01:46:01,849
All right.

1659
01:46:01,889 --> 01:46:03,653
Here's the deal. Just give me the facts.

1660
01:46:03,729 --> 01:46:05,060
Just the facts. Only the facts.

1661
01:46:05,129 --> 01:46:09,020
Breathe. Focus. Keep it simple.

1662
01:46:09,089 --> 01:46:10,739
No, no, no. No doubt, no doubt. Okay.

1663
01:46:10,849 --> 01:46:13,216
So, I'm at this art museum
with my cousin Ignacio, right?

1664
01:46:13,289 --> 01:46:15,529
<i>And there was this, like,
abstract expressionism exhibit.</i>

1665
01:46:15,569 --> 01:46:17,810
<i>But you know me, I'm more
like a Neo-Cubist kind of guy, right?</i>

1666
01:46:17,889 --> 01:46:20,574
<i>But there was this one Rothko
that was sublime, bro! Oh, my God!</i>

1667
01:46:20,689 --> 01:46:22,817
- Luis.
- Okay, sorry. Sorry.

1668
01:46:22,889 --> 01:46:24,891
You know, I just get excited and stuff.

1669
01:46:24,969 --> 01:46:26,937
<i>But anyway, Ignacio tells me,</i>

1670
01:46:27,009 --> 01:46:30,650
<i>"Yo, I met this crazy-fine writer chick
at the Spot last night. Like fine-fine.</i>

1671
01:46:30,729 --> 01:46:33,096
<i>"Like crazy-stupid fine." And he
goes up to the bartender and goes,</i>

1672
01:46:33,169 --> 01:46:34,853
<i>"Look at the girl I'm with.
You know what I'm sayin'?</i>

1673
01:46:34,929 --> 01:46:36,249
<i>"She's crazy-stupid fine, right?"</i>

1674
01:46:36,289 --> 01:46:38,940
<i>The bartender's all like,
"Yeah, crazy-stupid fine."</i>

1675
01:46:39,009 --> 01:46:40,932
<i>So this writer chick tells Ignacio,</i>

1676
01:46:41,009 --> 01:46:43,819
<i>"Yo, I'm like a boss
in the world of guerrilla journalism,</i>

1677
01:46:43,889 --> 01:46:45,618
<i>"and I got mad connects
with the peeps behind the curtains,</i>

1678
01:46:45,689 --> 01:46:46,656
<i>"you know what I'm saying?"</i>

1679
01:46:46,729 --> 01:46:48,254
<i>Ignacio's like, "For real?"</i>

1680
01:46:48,329 --> 01:46:51,299
<i>And she's like, "Yeah, you know what,
I can't tell you who my contact is,</i>

1681
01:46:51,369 --> 01:46:52,734
<i>"because he works with the Avengers."</i>

1682
01:46:52,849 --> 01:46:54,135
Oh, no.

1683
01:46:54,209 --> 01:46:56,610
Yeah, and this dude sounds
like a badass, man.

1684
01:46:56,689 --> 01:46:57,850
Like, he comes up to her and says,

1685
01:46:57,929 --> 01:46:59,977
<i>"Yo, I'm looking for this dude
who's new on the scene,</i>

1686
01:47:00,049 --> 01:47:01,175
<i>"who's flashing his fresh tack,</i>

1687
01:47:01,249 --> 01:47:03,820
<i>"who's got, like, bomb moves, right?
Who you got?"</i>

1688
01:47:03,889 --> 01:47:07,018
<i>And she's like, "Well, we got everything
nowadays. We got a guy who jumps.</i>

1689
01:47:07,089 --> 01:47:09,171
<i>"We got a guy who swings,
we got a guy who crawls up the walls.</i>

1690
01:47:09,249 --> 01:47:10,978
<i>"You gotta be more specific."</i>

1691
01:47:11,049 --> 01:47:12,892
<i>And he's like,
"I'm looking for a guy that shrinks."</i>

1692
01:47:12,969 --> 01:47:16,416
And I'm, like, "Damn!" I got all nervous
'cause I'd keep mad secrets for you, bro.

1693
01:47:16,489 --> 01:47:17,536
So I asked Ignacio,

1694
01:47:17,609 --> 01:47:19,657
<i>"Did the badass tell
the stupid-fine writer chick</i>

1695
01:47:19,729 --> 01:47:21,970
"to tell you to tell me,
because I'm tight with Ant-Man,

1696
01:47:22,049 --> 01:47:23,289
